SEAIT Anti Cheat Quiz: AI-Driven Adaptive Quiz System with Intelligent Anti-Cheating Detection for Improving College Learning and Assessment at South East Asian Institute of Technology.
Quantitative:

drivin - use ai to make decisions automatically 
adaptive - the qiuz change depending on student performance.


1. Suspicious Behavior Pattern Detection.
Extremely fast answering time
Sudden perfect score after previous low scores
Identical answer pattern between students
Multiple tab switching behavior
Student answers 30 questions in 1 minute

2. Adaptive Question Randomization
AI:
Shuffles question order
Changes question difficulty
Randomizes choices


3. Instructor Question Generator
Allows instructors to upload learning materials such as PDF, Word, PowerPoint, or text documents, and the system automatically analyzes the content using AI to generate quiz questions based on key concepts,
definitions, and important topics extracted from the file. The generated questions may include multiple choice, true or false, identification, and situational types,
which the instructor can review, edit, adjust the difficulty level, and save to the question bank before assigning them to students.


4. Post-Quiz Ranking and Score Transparency

After completing the quiz, the system automatically computes and displays each studentâ€™s score, percentile rank,
and overall class ranking based on total performance, completion time, and accuracy rate. Students can immediately view their individual results,
while instructors can access a ranked list of all students to analyze comparative performance using quantitative metrics such as mean score,
highest score, lowest score, and overall class performance distribution.


5. Quiz-Based Coin Reward and Character Customization

After completing each quiz, students earn coins based on the number of correct answers, quiz difficulty, and completion time. These coins can be accumulated and used to unlock or purchase character customizations, avatars, and other in-platform virtual items. This gamified system motivates students to perform better, encourages engagement, and allows instructors to track quantitative metrics such as coins earned, quizzes completed, and correlation between quiz performance and rewards.










